DocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hoa1665702732769.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hoa1665702732769.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hoa1665702732769.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hoa1665702732769\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      map fixed length to variable\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Map fields with a fixed length storage format (CHAR) to a variable length storage format.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__topic_d55778e1_d55779e1_d55780e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__p_d55781e1_d55782e1_d55783e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$ORA_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n                                map fixed length to variable</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__p_d55784e1_d55785e1_d55786e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$ORA_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n                                fv</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__section_w5t_3n4_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1060766e72\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__p_d55790e1_d55791e1_d55792e1\">This setting can greatly reduce the disk space\n            required for large table sets. However, it may also reduce the database performance by\n            20%-50%.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hoa1665702732769__p_d55793e1_d55794e1_d55795e1\">This setting maps the Oracle storage format\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">CHAR</code> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">VARCHAR2</code>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dpf1665702961248.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Oracle Data Packing</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528307\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528307\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "map fixed length to variable Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 map fixed length to variable Map fields with a fixed length storage format (CHAR) to a variable length storage format. USYS$ORA_PARAMS = map fixed length to variable USYS$ORA_PARAMS = fv Description This setting can greatly reduce the disk space required for large table sets. However, it may also reduce the database performance by 20%-50%. This setting maps the Oracle storage format CHAR to VARCHAR2 . Related Links Oracle Data Packing Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}